<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="scan-vt">scan <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /skæn/    美 /skæn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>细看</strong></h4>
<p>to examine every part carefully but quickly, because you’re looking for a particular person or thing：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>scan the first paragraph to find out the topic 
仔细阅读第一段以找出主题</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>浏览:</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He scanned the letter before he signed it.
他把信浏览了一遍，然后签了字。</p></div>

<h3 id="scan-skim-skip">辨析 scan, skim, skip</h3>
<p>scan, skim和skip是阅读文章时所采取的三种策略。<br />
<strong>scan ** 指通过快速阅读查找所需的某一特定信 息，意为“查读”。
</strong>skim ** 指通过快速阅读找到文章的中心思想， 意为“略读”。
**skip ** 指跳过即将阅读的某一部分内容，意为 “跳读”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Skip the first passage and start on Page 15. 
跳过第一篇文章从第15页开始看。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>扫描：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>scanning equipment 
扫描设备</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Tony is <strong><em>_</em></strong>__(浏览) the guidebook, looking for information about Japan, where he will travel soon.   （2003 上海）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. scanning  </p></div>